What is proven now
------------------

- speed/mass/caliber/cx/maxDistance are good live ammo reads
- velRange field in weapon props is not the decisive per-ammo runtime source
- global table manager tables are shared, not per-ammo
- actual projectile behaviour is generated at runtime through:
  FUN_0537e910 / FUN_0537f090 -> FUN_07268360 / FUN_07268480 -> triplet tables
- tested live ammo so far (1700 APFSDS, 905 HEAT, 850 HE) all reported:
  - model enum = 0
  - branch = model_0_direct
- therefore the current mismatch problem for tested APFSDS rounds is not explained by
  model 3/5/6 Mach-curve branches
- for these tested model_0 rounds, the most useful live runtime seed is:
  - speed
  - mass
  - caliber
  - cx
  - derived drag_k = (cx * area) / mass
- practical overlay implication:
  - model_0_direct should use memread-driven drag_k as the primary drag seed
  - velRange shaping should not be trusted as the decisive source for those rounds
  - current overlay heuristic adds a model_0_direct subcaliber sensitivity scale from:
    - speed delta vs 1500 m/s reference
    - caliber delta vs 0.016 m reference
  - reason:
    - tested 1700 APFSDS stayed on model_0_direct but still mismatched more than 1500 APFSDS
    - so linear drag_k/base_k alone was not sufficient for overlay parity


